 /*
-    Placeholder Linux backend: no real window is created yet. Every entry point returns a safe,
-    inert default so the rest of the engine can link and run without an OS window.
+    X11 (Xlib) backend. The window handle stored in m_hwnd is the X11 Window id; the Vulkan
+    swapchain creates a VkXlibSurfaceKHR from it (window ids are global on the X server, so the
+    swapchain's own display connection can address windows created here).
+
+    Key events are translated to Windows virtual key codes, which is what the script layer
+    expects on every platform (see Scancodes.h).
+*/
